orts a two\ncomponent interpretation of the data.\n  Irrespective of the detailed interpretation of the spectral properties, these\ndata support the presence of accretion onto a stellar mass black hole in a LMXB\naccreting in the Eddington-regime. This allows an unambiguous connection of\nthis object, and, by extension, similar low luminosity ULXs, to `standard'\nX-ray binaries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Nov 2011 17:14:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-03"}
